00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:16,588
if we have any clans that are not feuding, because this

187
00:12:16,649 --> 00:12:20,112
response wouldn't make any sense if we don't have anyone

188
00:12:20,132 --> 00:12:21,013
we could trade it to.

189
00:12:23,195 --> 00:12:25,617
As the script executes, the first thing that happens is a

190
00:12:25,657 --> 00:12:26,738
choose clan function.

191
00:12:27,359 --> 00:12:29,601
And that just puts up user interface where the player

192
00:12:29,701 --> 00:12:30,882
gets to choose a clan.

193
00:12:32,882 --> 00:12:39,804
Once they do that, we start doing things like looking at the relationship with that clan

194
00:12:39,824 --> 00:12:43,624
that the player picked and calculating a modifier.

195
00:12:45,345 --> 00:12:51,406
There's also modifiers based on your own allocation of clan magic and just as a shorthand where

